  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "The ***speaker*** is the voice that addresses the reader in a [poem](../../../terms/poem.md) — the \"I\" (explicit or implied) who perceives, reflects, and speaks. The speaker is to poetry what the [narrator](../../fiction/terms/narrator.md) is to fiction: the figure through whom the work is experienced. And like the narrator, the speaker is not the poet.",
